## LangGraph Service and LLM Integration

The heavy lifting for AI-driven features is handled by the **LangGraph service**, a Python application that runs separately from the Next.js web app. LangGraph is responsible for interfacing with language models (like OpenAI GPT) and processing the inputs into the desired outputs (estimates, answers, etc.). Itâ€™s designed so that the potentially slow or large computation (LLM calls, file downloading, etc.) happens off the main web thread. Hereâ€™s an overview of LangGraph and how it works:

